# Git Commit Guidelines

## When to Push
- ✅ Code changes that affect functionality
- ✅ Bug fixes
- ✅ New features
- ✅ Configuration changes needed for deployment

## When NOT to Push (or commit separately)
- ❌ Documentation-only changes (.md files)
- ❌ Comment-only changes
- ❌ Temporary debug files
- ❌ Scratch/notes files

## Workflow
1. Make code changes
2. Commit code changes
3. Make documentation changes separately (don't push immediately)
4. Only push when code is ready for deployment


